We had visited Rome twice before and are well aware that most of the rooms and bathrooms are small by American standards.	The breakfast is good by Rome standards, but if you're expecting eggs & bacon, you won't find it.	Of course if you need American standards of large rooms and a full breakfast then this is not the place for you.	The prices in Rome are very high by US standards.	Rooms are spacious ( for European standards), quite and super clean.	The double rooms are perfect for our needs with good showers, large flat screen TV's, and Wifi.